The**Order Fulfilled**trigger starts a flow when an order is marked as fulfilled, meaning the products have been shipped or delivered to the customer.**Note:**This Trigger is a part of [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce) Integration**Topics Covered:**[How to Configure Order Fulfilled Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780115349785-Order-Fulfilled#h_01J8H8W94Z4C05TK6RYJ3AYFNR)[Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780115349785-Order-Fulfilled#h_01J8H8ZCQJF6343V1PM5G02TT7)

### How to Configure Order Fulfilled Trigger

While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Order Fulfilled**trigger.

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-16.png)

When setting up the**Order Fulfilled**trigger, you'll need to configure the following:**Name:**Provide a clear, descriptive name for the trigger.**Description:**Write a brief explanation of the trigger's function.**Select Store:**Choose the**BigCommerce Store**where the order fulfillment process is tracked.**Contact:**Add contact-related conditions such as email, phone number, or other customer attributes that should match before the trigger is activated.**BigCommerce:**Add specific BigCommerce conditions related to the order fulfillment process. This allows the trigger to activate for specific types of orders or customerOnce the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![mceclip1.png](./images/mceclip1-16.png)

### Practical Example

Let's create a Smart Flow to nurture your customers once the order placed by them was finally delivered. We'll first out an email saying 'The order was successfully Delivered', upon that we'll Add a delay of say about a day and send out another email asking for the Product Feedback, that they ordered and rate their Shopping Experience.
